                  <interp inst="t18220220-35-crimeloc188" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-35-crimeloc188" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-35-off186 t18220220-35-crimeloc188"></join>, <rs id="t18220220-35-viclabel189" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-35-victim441 t18220220-35-viclabel189"></join>. On the 21st of January, between two and three o'clock; the prisoner came in alone, and asked to look at black worsted stockings, at 15 d. per pair. I shewed her some which did not suit her, she bid me 1 s., which I refused; she moved towards the counter, laid hold of some handkerchiefs, and asked the price. I was serving a gentleman, and asked her to wait. I was obliged to go to the back of the shop for stockings for the gentleman, and was detained about five minutes by him. On coming to the front, the prisoner was going away, and directly she left the shop I missed a piece of handkerchief. I went after her, found her about one hundred yards off, and saw them peeping out from under a bundle which she had. I found it was my master's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-35-person444">
                  GEORGE 
                  WATTS
               <interp inst="t18220220-35-person444" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
